              <head>Dictionaries</head>
              <div>
                  <head>Data</head>
                  
                  <p xml:space="preserve">All entries in the dictionaries which are not further indicated are
        taken from data provided by the collaborator(s) cited on the front
        page of each dictionary. Data extracted from other published sources
        is indicated as such and includes the respective reference.</p>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                  <head>Transcription</head>
                  
                  <p xml:space="preserve">The transcription follows a system which is widely accepted in
        Arabic studies and also used in reference works such as the
        Encyclopedia of Arabic Language and Linguistics (Leiden: Brill,
        2006-2009).</p>
                  
                  <p xml:space="preserve">Following a widespread convention in Arabic dialectology, the data
        is presented in in a broad phonological transcription that does not
        indicate allophones.</p>
                  
